@node "Proj_new" "New"


      This will clear the current display and reset to the default values.
@endnode

@node "Proj_load" "Load"



      Will call a file requester for you to choose a previously saved
      project with the .gt extension.
@endnode

@node "Proj_save" "Save"



       Saves a project in a format to enable it to be reloaded in the 
       future for further editing.
@endnode

@node "Proj_saveas" "Save as"



        Calls a file requester to enable you to choose a path and file 
        to @{"save" link "Proj_save" 0} the project to.
@endnode

@node "Proj_about" "About"



       Displays authors name, version number and arexx port name.
@endnode

@node "Proj_gencode" "GenCode"




        This will generate the Blitz Basic2 code needed to generate the
        GUI display in your own programs.
@endnode

@node "Proj_prefs" "Prefs"



     This menu item enables you to change various items concerning 
   the @{"generated code" link "Proj_prefs_gencode" 0} and also how GUIToolKit looks and works(@{"general" link "Proj_prefs_general" 0}).
@endnode

@node "Proj_prefs_gencode" "generated code"




      Here you can enter the following settings that effect the final
      code that is generated.  This information is saved with the 
      project.

      1. Screen id
      2. Window id
      3. Gadget list id
      4. Project title.
      5. Re-number the gadgets Id's in the order they appear in the list
         each time the code is generated (Default = no).
      6. Re-sort the gadgets Id's each time the code is generated 
         (Default = yes). 
      7. Use palette in generated code (Default = no).
@endnode

@node "Proj_prefs_general" "general"



      To save how the program looks and other settings select this menu
      item.
@endnode

@node "Proj_quit" "Quit"



    Quits the progam of course!
@endnode

@node "Scrn_palette" "Palette"



   From this window you can change the current palette using the sliders
   etc. Load and save palettes and by selecting "Yes - use palette" in 
   the Prefs/code requester the code for using that palette will be 
   inserted in the "generated code".
@endnode

@node "Scrn_Type" "Type"


      Here you can choose a any screen mode from the requester, interlaced
      or not interlaced. Specify the width and height, the number of
      bit-planes, the title for the screen and a choise of 

          Workbench - open the window on the workbench screen.
          Custom    - set up your own screen for your own use.
          Current   - open on the currently used screen.
          Public    - not yet available.
@endnode

@node "Win_Name" "Name"


      Here you can alter the Windows title.
@endnode

@node "Win_Attrib" "Attrib"



     This controls what system gadgets and properties the window will 
     have.  They are -

     1. Sizing gadget.
     2. Drag bar.
     3. Depth gadget.
     4. Close gadget.
     5. Size right.
     6. Size bottom.
     7. Backdrop.
     8. Gimmezerozero.
     9. Borderless.
     10. Active.

     Just check mark the one's you want.
@endnode

@node "Win_IDCMP" "IDCMP"


       This configures what events your window wants to know about.
       See the Blitz manual or ROM Kernal Libraries book for more
       details.

       You can choose between 3 options -
       1. Use the default setting, no code is generated.
       2. Custom settings, depending on what you select or deselect
          IDCMP flags are added to or tacken awey from the default.
       3. Use as default, your selection will be set as the default
          for this and any following windows.
@endnode

